Here are the public test cases for feature11_run_as_same_id:
{
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "run_as_same_user": "false",
        "op": "run_as_same_id"
      },
      "expected_output": "{\"result\":false,\"run_as_user\":100,\"status\":\"ok\"}\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "app_run_as_user": 123456,
        "run_as_same_user": "true",
        "op": "run_as_same_id"
      },
      "expected_output": "{\"result\":true,\"run_as_user\":123456,\"status\":\"ok\"}\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "run_as_same_user": "true",
        "op": "run_as_same_id"
      },
      "expected_output": "{\"error\":\"not_allowed\",\"result\":false,\"run_as_user\":100,\"status\":\"error\"}\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "run_as_same_user": "rooooooot",
        "op": "run_as_same_id"
      },
      "expected_output": "{\"error\":\"not_allowed\",\"result\":false,\"run_as_user\":100,\"status\":\"error\"}\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "app_run_as_user": 0,
        "run_as_same_user": "true",
        "op": "run_as_same_id"
      },
      "expected_output": "{\"error\":\"not_allowed\",\"result\":false,\"run_as_user\":100,\"status\":\"error\"}\n"
    }
  ],
  "description": "Decide whether the agent container should run as the same user id as the application container. The decision is driven by a run-as-same-user flag and the application's declared run-as user id. When the flag is true and the app declares a non-root id, the agent adopts that id (result true). When the flag is false or unset, the agent keeps its default id (result false). When the flag is true but the app declares no id, or declares root (0), or when the flag value is not a valid boolean, it is reported as the error category not_allowed with the agent id left at its default."
}

